               <p>
                  <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="182704050039"></xptr>
            
                  <persName id="t18270405-68-person473">
                  PETER 
                  PLUMBLEY
               <interp inst="t18270405-68-person473" type="surname" value="PLUMBLEY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270405-68-person473" type="given" value="PETER"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270405-68-person473" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am shopman to David Simpson - he is a <rs id="t18270405-68-viclabel386" type="occupation">glover and haberdasher</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18270405-68-victim472 t18270405-68-viclabel386"></join>; the prisoner was about two months in his service. On the 29th of March, about eleven o'clock in the morning, a young man informed me that a paper of gloves was removed from a recess - I searched, and found them secreted on a form which was suspended from the ceiling of the cellar - there were sixteen pairs in the paper; I marked three or four pairs, and also the paper, and at five o'clock in the afternoon I found they were moved. I found the prisoner in custody at half-past five, with them.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined by MR. ADOLPHUS. Q. How long have you lived with Mr. Simpson? A. Five months - he has no partner. The gloves were not laid in the recess to see if any body would take them.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18270405-68-person474">
                  THOMAS 
                  HERDSFIELD
               <interp inst="t18270405-68-person474" type="surname" value="HERDSFIELD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270405-68-person474" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270405-68-person474" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a constable. I had been watching this house for two days, by direction of Mr. Simpson. I saw the prisoner come out between five and six o'clock - I pushed him up a passage, and took out of his breeches this parcel of gloves; he said he had picked them up behind the counter.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18270405-68-verdict387" type="verdictDescription">
